# Decisions & Learnings

Chronological log of decisions, learnings, and insights. Automatically maintained — read on demand, append in real-time.

This file serves as the project's **decision trail**: every choice, discovery, and course correction is logged here as it happens, not just at session end. This makes it possible to trace *why* something is the way it is, weeks or months later.

## How this file is maintained

- **Automatic**: Claude logs entries here during the session whenever a decision is made or something important is learned — no explicit command needed
- **On save**: `/session save --learn` reviews the session for any decisions that weren't captured yet
- **Manual**: You can always ask Claude to log something: "log this decision" / "merke dir das"

## Format

### Decisions

```
### YYYY-MM-DD — [Short title]

**Decision:** [What was decided]
**Rationale:** [Why — the key reason]
**Alternatives considered:** [What else was evaluated, and why it lost]
**Context:** [What triggered this decision — the problem or question]
```

### Learnings & Discoveries

```
### YYYY-MM-DD — [Short title]

**Discovery:** [What was found out]
**Impact:** [Why it matters — what it affects]
**Source:** [How it was discovered — file, error, test, etc.]
```

### Course Corrections

```
### YYYY-MM-DD — [Short title]

**Changed from:** [Previous approach]
**Changed to:** [New approach]
**Why:** [What went wrong or what new information emerged]
```

